For example, a resource like http://example.org/r2 might have the following RDF content with a self- reference: <http://example.org/r2> dc:description "something" .
In the given example, the content would then look like this: <http://example.org/r2.

Then we can replace the placeholder by the calculated artifact code and we end up with a trusty URI like this: http://example.org/r2.RAi7LA7Zlew99hdp0joN0APT4_uB3XDFwduiKXnNBja5E For strong hashing algorithms, it is impossible in practice that this calculated sequence of bytes was already part of the original content before the transfor- mation.
